        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 7:04PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 704 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Blacksville, or over
McDonough. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
McDonough, Hampton, Lovejoy, Blacksville, Bonanza, Atlanta Motor
Speedway, and Irondale.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
